ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.20.Live.PDTV.x264-NX

Saturday 26th July 2014 ITV4
2pm to 5pm Live

Stage 20 - the one and only individual time trial in the 2014 Tour de France comes on the penultimate day of the race. If the mountains have not already decided the winner then this stage will be critical in the battle for yellow. A rolling 54km between Bergerac and Perigueux, it is not a course necessarily suited to the specialists in the discipline like Martin or Cancellara, so quite a few riders could be in with a chance of glory today. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
